==English==

===Etymology===
French ''brunette'', feminine of ''brunet'', brown

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-notcomp}}

#Of a woman or girl, having dark brown hair.

====Translations====

{{top}}
*German: [[brünett]]
*Irish: [[donn]] (of males and females), [[fear#Irish|fear]] donn {{m}}, [[bean#Irish|bean]] dhonn {{f}}
*Italian: [[castana]] or [[castana]] scura
{{mid}}
*[[Scots Gaelic]]: [[donn]] & [[dorcha]] (of males and females), [[fear#Scots Gaelic|fear]] donn/dorcha {{m}}, [[bean#Scottish Gaelic|bean]] dhonn/dhorcha {{f}}
{{bottom}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#A woman or girl with black or brown hair.
